<title>CHINA: Liu Chong Hing interim net up 22 pct.</title>
<headline>Liu Chong Hing interim net up 22 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-08-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months ended June 30</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   80.0     vs 65.6</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    20.0     vs 18.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  nil	vs nil</p>
<p>    Net			    304.44   vs 249.53</p>
<p>    Turnover		     2,276.70 vs 1,102.53 (see note)</p>
<p>    Company name		 Liu Chong Hing Investment Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  September 8-12</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   September 19</p>
<p>NOTE - Liu Chong Hing engages in property development and investment, warehousing, banking and insurance services.</p>
<p>Turnover for the period includes interest income, commissions, fees and other revenue earned from banking operations. Comparative figures have been adjusted to conform with the current year's presentation.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
